                <h1>Go and Make Disciples: The Great Commission Explained</h1>
                <p>The phrase "go and make disciples" originates from the Great Commission in Matthew 28:19-20, where Jesus instructs His followers to spread His teachings globally. This command emphasizes the importance of sharing faith, fostering spiritual growth, and building community among believers, marking a central mission for the church throughout history.</p>
